Design and Implementation of a Controlled Phishing Email Simulation Framework

   Domain: Cyber Security & Ethical Hacking  
   Internship Project Report  
   Authors: **Susmitha C** & **NithyaShree T**

[Simulation Workflow Lifecycle]
Admin Controls -> Provision VPS -> Sign DNS Keys -> Send Tracking Phish -> Intercept Input -> Micro-Learning Page


## 🚀 Key Features
- **High-Fidelity Clone Profiles:** Custom HTML modules designed to resemble modern enterprise tools (e.g., Microsoft Teams alerts, IT password updates).
- **Privacy-First Data Flow:** The server intercepts POST requests, registers user failure metrics, and discards all plain-text inputs instantly to ensure confidentiality.
- **Granular Event Telemetry:** Measures exact user behavior metrics including email delivery success, open tracking via clear pixel tokens, link clicks, and time elapsed.
- **Just-in-Time Security Training:** Redirects users who interact with the simulation to a responsive educational landing page that flags specific indicators of deception.

## 🛠️ Tech Stack & Architecture
- **Base Infrastructure Engine:** GoPhish Core Platform Engine (Customized Routing Profiles)
- **Deployment OS Environment:** Linux Ubuntu TLS Node (Cloud Hosting VPS)
- **Routing & Proxy Services:** Nginx Server Layer (SSL Termination & Rate Control)
- **Data Ingestion Engine:** SQLite / PostgreSQL Relational Database
- **Automation Layers:** Python 3 & Bash Script Engines

