📋 Installation & Local Setup
1. Initialize Infrastructure Host
Connect to your deployed VPS node and update local system packages:

Bash
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y
sudo apt install nginx git python3-pip -y
2. Configure Domain Security Keys
Ensure your testing domain points to your host IP, then check your public DNS configurations for core identity compliance records:

Bash
# Verify your DKIM, SPF, and DMARC text parameters
dig txt yoursimulationdomain.com
3. Clone and Initialize Core Application Files
Bash
git clone [https://github.com/yourusername/phishing-simulation-framework.git](https://github.com/yourusername/phishing-simulation-framework.git)
cd phishing-simulation-framework
pip install -r automation-utilities/requirements.txt
